        <div class="fourth-page">
        <h1>
            All the features you'll ever need to manage your business
            
        </h1>
       
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-3 g-4">
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Category" asp-action="Index">
                   <div class="card-header">
                    <img src="/images/category.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                    <h2>Categories</h2>
                </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text">Categories in inventory management are used to group similar products for organization and management purposes. It makes tracking inventory levels, reordering and identifying slow-moving or excess stock easier and also improves customer's shopping experience.</p>
                    </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                     <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Supplier" asp-action="Index">
                    <div class="card-header">
                    <img src="/images/supplier.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                    <h2>Suppliers</h2>
                </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="card-text">Suppliers provide goods and materials for an inventory management website to track and manage. Inventory allows to add, track and manage supplier information and orders, generate supplier performance reports. Effective supplier management ensures inventory flow and smooth operations.</p>
                    </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Brand" asp-action="Index">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <img src="/images/brand.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                            <h2>Brands</h2>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text">Brands are used in inventory management to group and organize products, track sales performance, and stock levels. It also helps to identify counterfeit products and creates a more user-friendly shopping experience for customers by allowing them to find products by specific brands.</p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="PurchaseOrder" asp-action="Index">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <img src="/images/purchasing-icon-17.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                            <h2>Purchasing</h2>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text">In an inventory management system, purchasing plays a critical role in maintaining adequate stock levels, keeping costs under control, and ensuring that the products offered on the website are of high quality. An effective purchasing strategy can help to minimize stockouts, reduce overstocking and ultimately improve customer satisfaction.</p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Product" asp-action="Index">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <img src="/images/producti.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                            <h2>Products</h2>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text">Keeping track of products and their corresponding details allows for better management of inventory levels, tracking of sales performance and reordering items as needed. Product information can also be used to create a more user-friendly shopping experience for customers by providing them with detailed product information and images.</p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="ProductGroup" asp-action="Index">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <img src="/images/group.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                            <h2>Product Groups</h2>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text">These groups could be based on various factors such as product type, brand, or even sales performance. Product groups can be used to track inventory levels, reorder items as needed, and identify slow-moving or excess stock. It can also make it easier for customers to find the product they want by browsing through the product groups.</p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

